& [SourceBackedBoundary] is the external research boundary
  + [clay_statement] is P vs NP asks whether every language accepted by a nondeterministic polynomial-time algorithm is also accepted by a deterministic polynomial-time algorithm
    = source: https://www.claymath.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/pvsnp.pdf
  + [clay_overview] is the intuitive distinction is easy checking versus easy solving
    = source: https://www.claymath.org/millennium/p-vs-np/
  + [np_complete_anchor] is SAT is the standard NP-complete contact point because NP problems reduce to SAT in polynomial time
    = source: https://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~shuchi/courses/787-F07/scribe-notes/lecture09.pdf
  + [barrier_caution] is separation attempts must respect relativization, natural proofs, and algebrization-style barriers
    = source: https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/1490270.1490272

& [CandidateRows] is the first target table
  + [row_001_sat_or_3sat] is highest proof-relevance target
    = np_membership_shape: truth assignment certificate verified by evaluating clauses
    = np_complete_contact: direct through SAT or 3-SAT NP-completeness
    = structural_fit: medium because phase locking can mean satisfying local constraints consistently
    = proof_route: P equals NP route if a deterministic polynomial-time solver is proved for all instances
    = main_lock: source gives no clause-language, no solver, and no worst-case runtime proof
    = priority: high
  + [row_002_constraint_satisfaction] is best semantic fit target
    = np_membership_shape: assignment certificate checked against local constraints
    = np_complete_contact: many CSP families are NP-complete, while restricted templates can be tractable
    = structural_fit: high because local coherence and correction-field language map naturally to constraints
    = proof_route: subclass route unless NP-complete CSP scope is specified
    = main_lock: must avoid proving only a tractable fragment while claiming P equals NP
    = priority: high_as_inquiry_medium_as_solution
  + [row_003_hamiltonian_path_or_cycle] is best traversal-language target
    = np_membership_shape: candidate path/cycle checked for adjacency and no repeated vertices
    = np_complete_contact: standard NP-complete graph target
    = structural_fit: high because the source emphasizes walking, anchors, and paths
    = proof_route: P equals NP route if all instances are solved in deterministic polynomial time
    = main_lock: resonance traversal needs a graph invariant that provably finds or rejects paths for worst-case graphs
    = priority: medium_high
  + [row_004_clique_or_independent_set] is structure-density target
    = np_membership_shape: candidate vertex set checked pairwise for required edge condition
    = np_complete_contact: standard NP-complete graph target
    = structural_fit: medium because phase coherence can map to dense mutual compatibility
    = proof_route: algorithm route or lower-bound route
    = main_lock: known worst-case graphs defeat naive structure heuristics
    = priority: medium
  + [row_005_pi_digit_traversal] is outside proof target
    = np_membership_shape: no NP decision language supplied
    = np_complete_contact: none
    = structural_fit: high as metaphor, low as P vs NP target
    = proof_route: toy laboratory only
    = main_lock: computing or predicting digits of pi does not address NP-complete decision problems
    = priority: outside_for_proof
  + [row_006_lower_bound_separation] is P not equals NP route
    = np_membership_shape: choose an NP language and prove no deterministic polynomial-time algorithm exists
    = np_complete_contact: can use SAT or another NP-complete language
    = structural_fit: low for current source text because it argues solvability, not hardness
    = proof_route: barrier-aware lower-bound theory
    = main_lock: no lower-bound framework is proposed
    = priority: low_currently

& [Conclusion] is the target-selection result
  + [best_next_target] is SAT/3-SAT or CSP, depending whether the next pass prioritizes maximum proof relevance or maximum semantic fit
  + [recommended_path] is start with CSP as semantic translation, then require SAT/3-SAT NP-complete contact before any P equals NP significance is claimed
  + [proposition_adjustment] is source resonance language may become a constraint-consistency heuristic, not a P vs NP proof, unless it solves an NP-complete target in polynomial time
  + [deep_research_gate] is deferred
    = reason: formal target-selection is now sharper; deep research should fire next only if CSP dichotomy, SAT solver lower bounds, or barrier theory becomes the active low-resolution blocker
  + [heartbeat_status] is active every minute
